============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Gini Coefficient
Category:   Statistics
Definition: Measures income inequality from 0 (equal) to 1 (one person has all)
Formula:    G = 1 - 2∫L(x)dx
Economist:  Corrado Gini
Example:    USA Gini ~0.41; Denmark ~0.29; South Africa ~0.63

Concept:    Keynesian Economics
Category:   Macroeconomics
Definition: Government fiscal policy stabilizes economy in recessions
Formula:    AD = C + I + G + NX
Economist:  John Maynard Keynes
Example:    2009 US stimulus; 2020-2021 COVID relief spending

Concept:    Comparative Advantage
Category:   International Trade
Definition: Countries gain by specializing in what they produce most efficiently
Formula:    Compare opportunity cost ratios
Economist:  David Ricardo
Example:    China makes electronics cheaply; USA makes pharma cheaply; both gain trading

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Taylor Series
Branch:       Calculus
Formula:      f(x) = sum of f^n(a)/n! * (x-a)^n
Applications: Numerical computation, signal processing
Discoverer:   Brook Taylor (1715)

Theorem/Law:  Central Limit Theorem
Branch:       Statistics
Formula:      Sample means approach normal distribution
Applications: Polling, quality control, finance
Discoverer:   Lyapunov (1901)

Theorem/Law:  Pythagorean Theorem
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      a² + b² = c²
Applications: Navigation, construction, computer graphics
Discoverer:   Pythagoras (500)

